The paper proposes an approach for query-based video summarization using deep neural networks, which suggests that it is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories. The approach also involves capturing the semantics of queries, which suggests that it may also belong to the information retrieval (cs.IR) and natural language processing (cs.CL) sub-categories. Finally, the paper evaluates the effectiveness of the approach, which suggests that it may also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category.
